---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Coming Home';
const subtitle = 'For days when you feel anxious, scattered, or unsafe in your body.';
const duration = '2 Hours · 7:00 – 9:00';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude-page">
    <header class="etude-head">
      <p class="etude-kicker">Etude · Restorative</p>
      <h1 class="etude-title">{title}</h1>
      <p class="etude-relief">{subtitle}</p>
      <p class="etude-duration">{duration}</p>
      <nav class="etude-nav">
        <a href="/etudes/restorative/">← restorative etudes</a>
        <span class="etude-nav-sep">·</span>
        <a href="/essays/the-partition-problem/">essay</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="etude-intro">
      <p class="etude-step">When to reach for this routine</p>
      <p>You woke up with your chest tight and your mind already three moves ahead. Or something happened yesterday — a conversation, a memory, a moment on the street — and your body is still braced for it. You may feel hypervigilant, like the world is too loud or too close. You might have trouble sitting still, or you might feel frozen. Either way, the nervous system is running hot and needs to be brought back to ground. This routine is pure safety: every pose is low, supported, and weighted toward the earth. Start here when the question is not "what should I do?" but "am I okay right now?"</p>
    </section>

    <div class="etude-stage">
      <section class="etude-card etude-card-segment">
        <p class="etude-step">Warm-Ups (Optional)</p>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Gentle neck circles, shoulder rolls, slow lateral stretches. Move without urgency — like branches swaying in a light wind. Let the breath lengthen naturally.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="etude-card etude-card-segment">
        <p class="etude-step">Pranayama · Dirga Pranayama (Three-Part Breath)</p>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Inhale into belly (roots), chest (trunk), collarbones (branches). Exhale top to bottom — long and slow. Five rounds, exhale twice as long as the inhale. The extended exhale signals the nervous system: you are safe right now.</p>
      </section>

      <p class="etude-section-label">Poses · Root to Crown</p>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Muladhara — I am here. I am safe. The ground holds me.</p>

      <section class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 1</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Balasana – Child’s Pose (Floor)</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">7:15 – 7:32</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-meta">Benefits – Deeply grounding; releases spine, hips, lower back; quiets the mind; may lower blood pressure; Root and Solar Plexus . Cautions – Hip or knee replacements; chronic back injuries; pregnancy; spondylolisthesis. Alt: Balasana – Chair or Reverse Chair Version.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“I relax from outer involvement into my inner haven of peace.”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-pose-body">Water moves softly over stones nearby as your chest opens toward the canopy — not to perform openness, but because the props are holding you that way and the body is grateful. Here, just for these minutes, the chest can soften; let the breath go all the way in.</p>
      </section>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Vishuddha → Ajna — I trust. I surrender to what is larger.</p>

      <section class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 2</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Viparita Karani – Waterfall</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">8:29 – 8:46</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-meta">Benefits – Drains excess fluid from legs; reduces exhaustion and fatigue; deeply calming for nervous and cardiovascular systems; may lower blood pressure. Cautions – Glaucoma; serious neck injuries; menstruation — teacher’s discretion; pregnancy after first trimester. Alt: Viparita Karani – Simple; Instant Maui.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“Awake, my sleeping powers, awake!”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-pose-body">Your legs rise like rivers toward the sky as the body begins its quiet work of repair — lymph moving, adrenals finally standing down. Something that has been braced for a long time is beginning to unknot; right now, you are safe.</p>
      </section>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Transition · Settling into Final Rest</p>

      <section class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 3</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Instant Maui</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">8:46 – 8:53</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-meta">Benefits – Drains excess fluid from legs; calming for nervous and cardiovascular systems; gentle bridge into final relaxation. Cautions – Adjust chair so knees are greater than 90 degrees. Avoid turning head in pose. Alt: Viparita Karani – Simple; remain in Waterfall.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“Awake, my sleeping powers, awake!”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-pose-body">The forest asks nothing of you — hands open like fallen leaves, water moves softly over stones, the trees breathe, you breathe, nothing to strive toward, nothing to solve. You are held completely. Rest here. You are home.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="etude-card etude-card-segment">
        <p class="etude-step">Exit cues</p>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Begin to sense your body and the room… Wiggle fingers and toes, gently rock the head side to side. Roll to one side and rest a moment like a river finding its bank. When ready, draw up to seated. A few minutes of meditative silence.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <footer class="etude-coda">
      <p>Let’s end by sending healing thoughts to the forests of this earth and to all living things. Visualize someone who needs the quiet strength of the forest today; surround them with that cool, green, steady energy… (pause)… Now wrap yourself in those same healing thoughts. Thank yourself for being here. Namaste.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  /* === etude page chrome === */
  .etude-page {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .etude-head {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .etude-kicker {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-relief {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .etude-duration {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .etude-nav {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .etude-nav a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .etude-nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-nav-sep { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }

  /* === intro === */
  .etude-intro {
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
  }
  .etude-intro .etude-step {
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }
  .etude-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* === stage === */
  .etude-stage {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* === micro labels === */
  .etude-step {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }

  /* === section divider label (Poses · Root to Crown) === */
  .etude-section-label {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.55rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  /* === chakra banner — small-caps label vocabulary === */
  .etude-chakra {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .etude-chakra-mark {
    margin-right: 0.45rem;
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  /* === pose / segment cards === */
  .etude-card {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.4rem;
  }
  .etude-card-segment {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem 1.2rem;
  }
  .etude-card-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-card-context {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .etude-pose-time {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    margin: 0 0 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .etude-pose-meta {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .etude-pose-quote {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0.85rem 0 1rem;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .etude-pose-body {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === coda === */
  .etude-coda {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-coda p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === mobile === */
  @media (max-width: 32rem) {
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
    .etude-card { padding: 1.15rem 1.1rem 1.1rem; border-radius: 10px; }
    .etude-card-segment { padding: 1rem 1.1rem; }
    .etude-card-title { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .etude-chakra { font-size: 0.78rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; }
    .etude-pose-quote { padding-left: 0.8rem; }
  }

  /* === print === */
  @media print {
    .etude-page {
      max-width: none;
      color: #000;
    }
    .etude-nav { display: none; }
    .etude-stage { gap: 0.6rem; }
    .etude-card,
    .etude-card-segment,
    .etude-chakra {
      background: transparent;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .etude-chakra {
      border: none;
      border-left: 3px solid #999;
      border-radius: 0;
      color: #000;
    }
    .etude-section-label {
      border-bottom: 1px solid #999;
      color: #000;
    }
    .etude-pose-quote {
      border-left: 2px solid #999;
    }
    .etude-coda {
      border-top: 1px solid #999;
    }
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    .etude-card-title { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>
